      "content": "IMPORTANT MAJOR INFORMATION",
      "contentHtml": null
    },
    {
      "id": "85ba6f45-6887-ef11-8474-000d3a37e3b6",
      "type": "GeneralText",
      "area": "General",
      "position": 1,
      "content": "The Russian Studies major allows students to learn the Russian language while studying economics, history, political science and other fields where Russian can be a plus. Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major. To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of the spring before transfer: One year of college level Russian OR At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was Russian. Completion of two years of college level foreign language is STRONGLY RECOMMENDED . A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses. All courses must be taken for a letter grade. For information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit https://slavic.ucla.edu and https://admission.ucla.edu . PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.",
      "contentHtml": "<p>The Russian Studies major allows students to learn the Russian language while studying economics, history, political science and other fields where Russian can be a plus.</p><p><br></p><p>Listed below are the lower division preparation courses for the major.</p><p><br></p><p>To be considered for this major, you must complete the following courses by the end of the spring before transfer:</p><ul><li>One year of college level Russian OR</li><li>At least one year of high school in which the primary language of instruction was Russian. </li></ul><p>Completion of two years of college level foreign language is <strong>STRONGLY RECOMMENDED</strong>. </p><p>A placement exam is required for all language majors regardless of credits earned in lower division language courses.</p><p>All courses must be taken for a letter grade.</p><p><br></p><p>For information regarding this major and UCLA's transfer selection process, visit <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://slavic.ucla.edu</u> and <u style=\"color: rgb(41, 98, 255);\">https://admission.ucla.edu</u>.</p><p><br></p><p>PLEASE NOTE: the community college courses listed below have been approved to satisfy the preparation for this major at UCLA, but they may not be exact equivalents of the UCLA courses listed.</p>"
    }
